{"comments":"Trigonometric functions — standard and hyperbolic.\n\nNo JavaScript. No FFI. Pure functional implementations using:\n- Taylor series for transcendental functions\n- Range reduction for numerical stability\n\n## Precision\n\nAll Taylor series use sufficient terms for IEEE 754 double precision\n(approximately 15-17 significant decimal digits).\n","declarations":[{"children":[],"comments":"Sine using Taylor series with range reduction\n\nsin(x) = x - x³/3! + x⁵/5! - x⁷/7! + ...\n\nRange reduction: reduce to [-π, π] then to [-π/2, π/2]\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[114,24],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Math/Core/Trigonometry.purs","start":[114,1]},"title":"sin"},{"children":[],"comments":"Cosine using Taylor series\n\ncos(x) = 1 - x²/2! + x⁴/4! - x⁶/6! + ...\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[153,24],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Math/Core/Trigonometry.purs","start":[153,1]},"title":"cos"},{"children":[],"comments":"Tangent\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}]